This paper deals with the fundamental limits of caching in heterogeneous networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). It also proposes an optimal delivery scheme, which involves network coding and transmission over a network, making it relevant to networking (cs.NI) and systems and control (cs.SI). The paper also involves optimization and mathematical analysis, which could fall under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
